HEADWORD: Stercorary
<hw>Ster"co*ra*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>stercorarium</ets>, from L. <ets>stercorarius</ets> belonging to
dung.]</ety> <def>A place, properly secured from the weather, for
containing dung.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stercorate</ent>⟦br⟧
